name: wheat bran to generic market for energy feed | energy feed, gross | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/20759/documentation

This activity is a linking activity, i.e. it connects wheat bran with generic protein feed market. Wheat bran is used partially as a feed for animals, thus traded on generic feed market with other protein - containing products.

The activity starts with the reception of wheat bran.

This linking activity has the wheat bran as an input (negative reference product) and protein and energy feed as outputs.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/108:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds/1080:Manufacture of prepared animal feeds

exchanges.description: Calculated based on literature values for "wheat bran" (Feedipedia, 2015), which reports a crude protein content of 17.3% of dry matter and a gross energy content equates to 18.9 MJ/kg dry matter of fed, with a dry matter content equates 87% of fed. Reference(s): Feedipedia (2015) Wheat Bran, Animal feed resources information system, Available at: https://www.feedipedia.org/node/726. (Accessed November 2017)
